
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [strings.replace] slot to replace occurrences of a placeholder string "[[link]]" within a target node's value, referenced by the expression [@.result], with the value of a node named [link] found within the [.arguments] node. The [get-value] slot retrieves this replacement value, allowing dynamic substitution based on the provided arguments.
strings.replace:x:@.result
   .:[[link]]
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/link
